ow/labels/area:graph","name":"area:graph","color":"5319e7","default":false,"description":"Module graph and dependency resolution"},{"id":11008033516,"node_id":"LA_kwDORpPJVM8AAAACkCFC7A","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fallow-rs/fallow/labels/type:correctness","name":"type:correctness","color":"d73a4a","default":false,"description":"Incorrect analysis result, silent failure, or false signal"},{"id":11008034146,"node_id":"LA_kwDORpPJVM8AAAACkCFFYg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fallow-rs/fallow/labels/priority:medium","name":"priority:medium","color":"fbca04","default":false,"description":"Useful next work but not immediately release-blocking"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-22T19:25:27Z","updated_at":"2026-05-24T08:08:01Z","closed_at":"2026-05-23T14:25:10Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nNode script entrypoints can be missed when package scripts use extensionless directory paths, and child-process entry scripts can be missed when passed through a static path variable. The Svelte repo has both patterns, and Fallow reports the runtime-used files as unused.\n\n## Evidence\n\nRunning the current local Fallow binary against a shallow checkout of `sveltejs/svelte` in `--production` mode reports these unused files:\n\n- `packages/svelte/scripts/process-messages/index.js`\n- `benchmarking/compare/runner.js`\n\nBut both are live runtime entrypoints:\n\n1. `packages/svelte/package.json` contains:\n\n```json\n\"dev\": \"node scripts/process-messages -w & rollup -cw\",\n\"generate\": \"node scripts/process-messages && node ./scripts/generate-types.js\"\n```\n\n`node scripts/process-messages` resolves to `scripts/process-messages/index.js` by Node's normal directory/index resolution.\n\n2. Root `package.json` contains:\n\n```json\n\"bench:compare\": \"NODE_ENV=production node --allow-natives-syntax ./benchmarking/compare/index.js\"\n```\n\n`benchmarking/compare/index.js` computes:\n\n```js\nconst runner = path.resolve(filename, '../runner.js')\n...\nfork(runner, [], { ... })\n```\n\n`runner.js` is therefore a child-process entrypoint, not an unused file.\n\nSource evidence:\n\n- https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/packages/svelte/package.json\n- https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/packages/svelte/scripts/process-messages/index.js\n- https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/package.json\n- https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/benchmarking/compare/index.js\n- https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/benchmarking/compare/runner.js\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nFallow should mark these files reachable:\n\n- Extensionless package-script file references should resolve with Node semantics, including directory `index.{js,mjs,cjs,ts}`.\n- `child_process.fork()` targets should be treated as dynamic entrypoints when the argument is a string literal or a statically-resolvable path variable.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\n- Extend package script entry resolution so `node scripts/process-messages` probes `scripts/process-messages.{js,mjs,cjs,ts,mts,cts}` and `scripts/process-messages/index.{js,mjs,cjs,ts,mts,cts}`.\n- Extend dynamic entry extraction for `child_process.fork(...)`, at least for:\n  - `fork('./runner.js')`\n  - `const runner = path.resolve(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url), '../runner.js'); fork(runner)`\n\nAcceptance fixture should mirror the Svelte package-script and benchmark-runner shapes and assert neither file is reported as unused.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fallow-rs/fallow/issues/638/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fallow-rs