pi.github.com/users/benbucksch/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/benbucksch/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":{"id":17595929,"node_id":"IT_kwDOCYj0A84BDH4Z","name":"Bug","description":"An unexpected problem or behavior","color":"red","created_at":"2024-02-14T00:23:49Z","updated_at":"2024-07-26T14:40:26Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Reproduction\n\n1. Open an email with a invitation \n\n### Actual Result\n\n- No errors thrown\n- UI freezes\n\n### Expected Result\n\n- Errors thrown if there's errors\n- UI doesn't freeze\n\n### Cause\n\nhttps://github.com/mustang-im/mustang/blob/b829872ae9f14d3604446b969f4075e223cc8040/app/frontend/Mail/Message/AttachmentsUI.svelte#L18-L19\n\nThis line causes an infinite loop which Svelte 5 doesn't handled.\n\n$: statements become $effect runes under the hood in Svelte 5 which updates and runs whenever there’s an update of value and that sometimes causes infinite loops and there’s no error thrown for these types of errors and error boundaries don’t work for this case.\n\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/issues/9944#issuecomment-1859255723\n\n\n### Possible Solutions\n\nTested and seems to work:\n\n- declaring attachments as a variable and wrapping it in a derived store\n- Using the derived rune","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mustang-im/mustang/issues/1207/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mustang-im/mustang/issues/1207/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/events","html_url":"https://github.com/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29","id":4371918048,"node_id":"I_kwDOQLtV4M8AAAABBJYs4A","number":29,"title":"Declare \"svelte\" field in package.json so SvelteKit auto-bundles for SSR","user":{"login":"stickerdaniel","id":63877413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYzODc3NDEz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/63877413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel","html_url":"https://github.com/stickerdaniel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-03T13:25:23Z","updated_at":"2026-05-06T06:26:07Z","closed_at":"2026-05-06T06:26:07Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"The published package does not declare a top-level `\"svelte\"` field in `package.json`. SvelteKit auto-adds dependencies with this field to `ssr.noExternal` (sveltejs/kit#1148, sveltejs/kit#904), which is required for Svelte component libraries that use runes or `svelte/internal/server` context APIs.\n\nWithout the field, SvelteKit externalizes the package during SSR. The package's compiled `setupAutumn` calls `useConvexClient` from `convex-svelte`, which calls `getContext` from a runtime-resolved svelte instance separate from the consumer's bundled svelte. With the next `convex-svelte` major (or any consumer using `@mmailaender/convex-svelte` directly), the dual-instance hazard surfaces as `lifecycle_outside_component` during prerender.\n\nSurfaced while bumping the better-auth ecosystem in `saas-starter` (stickerdaniel/saas-starter#343) — manual `ssr.noExternal` was added in vite.config.ts as a workaround.\n\n## Proposed fix\n\nAdd to `package.json`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"svelte\": \"./dist/svelte/index.js\"\n}\n```\n\nPath should match the primary Svelte entry. The `svelte` field is read directly by SvelteKit (separate from `exports`).\n\n## References\n\n- SvelteKit auto-bundling for Svelte component libraries: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/1148\n- Auto-detection via `svelte` field: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/904\n- Vite SSR options (`ssr.noExternal`): https://vite.dev/config/ssr-options.html#ssr-noexternal\n- SvelteKit packaging docs: https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/packaging","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28/events","html_url":"https://github.com/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28","id":4371917859,"node_id":"I_kwDOPNfD4M8AAAABBJYsIw","number":28,"title":"Declare \"svelte\" field in package.json so SvelteKit auto-bundles for SSR","user":{"login":"stickerdaniel","id":63877413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYzODc3NDEz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/63877413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel","html_url":"https://github.com/stickerdaniel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-03T13:25:19Z","updated_at":"2026-05-04T14:07:30Z","closed_at":"2026-05-04T14:02:32Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Follow-up to #25 with the actual root cause and a concrete fix. The package does not declare a top-level `\"svelte\"` field in `package.json`. SvelteKit auto-adds dependencies that declare this field to `ssr.noExternal`, which keeps Svelte runes and `svelte/internal/server` context APIs running against the same bundled svelte instance as the consumer's compiled `.svelte` output (sveltejs/kit#1148, sveltejs/kit#904).\n\nWithout the field, SvelteKit treats the package as external during SSR. Its `import { setContext } from 'svelte'` resolves to a separate svelte module instance from the route chunks. The two have independent module-scoped `ssr_context` variables, so `setContext` throws `lifecycle_outside_component` even though the call happens inside a `$$renderer.component()` callback.\n\nReproducible since 0.6 via `createSvelteAuthClient` -> `resolveConvexClient` -> `setupConvex` -> `setConvexClientContext` -> `setContext` on every prerendered route in any consumer app. Confirmed by instrumenting `node_modules/svelte/src/internal/server/context.js`: `ssr_context` is `null` at the failing call even though the layout's compiled chunk has set it on its own bundled copy.\n\n## Proposed fix\n\nAdd to `package.json`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"svelte\": \"./dist/svelte/index.js\"\n}\n```\n\nPath should match the package's primary Svelte entry. The `svelte` field is read directly by SvelteKit (separate from `exports`) to identify Svelte component libraries.\n\n## Consumer workaround until released\n\n```ts\n// vite.config.ts\nssr: {\n  noExternal: ['@mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte']\n}\n```\n\n## References\n\n- SvelteKit auto-bundling for Svelte component libraries: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/1148\n- Auto-detection via `svelte` field: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/904\n- Vite SSR options (`ssr.noExternal`): https://vite.dev/config/ssr-options.html#ssr-noexternal\n- SvelteKit packaging docs: https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/packaging","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/233","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/233/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/233/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/233/events","html_url":"https://github.com/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/233","id":4412980998,"node_id":"I_kwDOSYBYgc8AAAABBwi_Bg","number":233,"title":"Add Svelte sample app to VERIFY-2 corpus (sveltejs/realworld)","user":{"login":"cajasmota","id":5105329,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUxMDUzMjk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5105329?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cajasmota","html_url":"https://github.com/cajasmota","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cajasmota/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users