ttps://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/22841?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi","html_url":"https://github.com/jippi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jippi/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-05-23T11:39:43Z","updated_at":"2026-05-23T14:36:11Z","closed_at":"2026-05-23T14:36:11Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Describe the bug\n\nA leaf `+page.svelte` whose path nests inside **three or more** `(group)` segments — with a parametric ancestor above the groups — stops matching its bare URL on `@sveltejs/kit@2.61.0`. The route still appears in the route manifest and the param matcher is registered, but kit never selects the leaf at runtime; `event.route.id` is `null` and the layout above the leaf does not run.\n\nThe observable response shape depends on whether a sibling route happens to absorb the URL:\n\n- **`[[anything]]/+page.server.ts` sibling present**: kit selects the sibling instead of the leaf (since `[[ ]]` matches the bare URL with `anything = undefined`), runs its `load`, and surfaces whatever response that load produces. In the repro this becomes a silent **302**.\n- **`[anything]/+page.server.ts` sibling present**: the required `[ ]` cannot match an empty segment, so it doesn't absorb the URL — but `(meta)/+page.svelte` still doesn't match either. **404**.\n- **No sibling**: no route matches at all. **404**.\n\nIn all three 2.61.0 cases the leaf `(meta)/+page.svelte` is the route that should match — it just doesn't. Same code on `@sveltejs/kit@2.60.1` matches correctly in every variant.\n\nWe suspect [PR #15861](https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/15861) (\"avoid conflict for routes ending with optional parameters\") as the regression, but the underlying problem is broader than that PR's scope: the leaf doesn't match even when no `[[optional]]` sibling exists.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nMinimal repro repo: **<https://github.com/jippi/kit-2.61-route-group-bug>**\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/jippi/kit-2.61-route-group-bug\ncd kit-2.61-route-group-bug\npnpm install   # installs kit 2.61.0 — the broken version\npnpm dev\n```\n\nIn another shell:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sI http://localhost:5173/123 | head -1\n# kit 2.61.0:   HTTP/1.1 302 Found     (and Location: /)\n# kit 2.60.1:   HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n```\n\nTo confirm the 2.60.1 baseline:\n\n```bash\npnpm add -D @sveltejs/kit@2.60.1\nrm -rf .svelte-kit\npnpm dev\n# /123 now correctly renders (meta)/+page.svelte\n```\n\n## Demonstration matrix\n\nSame route tree across all six columns; only the sibling shape under `(meta)/` and the kit version vary.\n\n| URL         | 2.60.1 + `[[anything]]` | 2.60.1 + `[anything]` | 2.60.1 no sibling | 2.61.0 + `[[anything]]` | 2.61.0 + `[anything]` | 2.61.0 no sibling |\n| ----------- | ----------------------- | --------------------- | ----------------- | ----------------------- | --------------------- | ----------------- |\n| `/123`      | **200** ✅              | **200** ✅            | **200** ✅        | **302 → `/`** ❌        | **404** ❌            | **404** ❌        |\n| `/123/news` | 200 ✅                  | 200 ✅                | 200 ✅            | 200 ✅                  | 200 ✅                | 200 ✅            |\n| `/123/junk` | 302 → `/123` ✅         | 302 → `/123` ✅       | 404 ✅            | 302 → `/123` ✅         | 302 → `/123` ✅       | 404 ✅            |\n| `/`         | 200 ✅                  | 200 ✅                | 200 ✅            | 200 ✅                  | 200 ✅                | 200 ✅            |\n\nAll three 2.61.0 columns fail `/123`. The `[[anything]]` (optional) vs `[anything]` (required) bracket distinction only changes the failure mode (silent 302 vs visible 404) — neither restores the correct match. Sibling-specific routes (`/news`) are unaffected; the breakage is isolated to the bare `/{param}` URL whose only valid match is the deeply nested leaf.\n\n## Bisected conditions\n\n- **Three or more route groups around the leaf.** Removing the outer `(series)` group (so the path becomes `[id]/(view)/(meta)/+page.svelte`) makes `/123` match correctly on 2.61.0. Two route groups is not enough to trigger the regression.\n- **A parametric ancestor (`[id]`) above the groups.**\n- The leaf can be `+page.svelte` alone, or `+page.svelte` plus arbitrary sibling routes — the leaf does not match in any of the six configurations measured above.\n\n## Route tree (from the repro)\n\n```text\nsrc/routes/\n├── +layout.svelte\n├── +page.svelte                                              # /\n└── (series)/                                                 # <-- route group #1\n    └── [id]/                                                 # parametric segment\n        └── (view)/                                           # <-- route group #2\n            ├── +layout.svelte\n            ├── (meta)/                                       # <-- route group #3\n            │   ├── +page.svelte                              # /{id}            ← BROKEN on 2.61.0\n            │   └── [[anything]]/\n            │       └── +page.server.ts                       # /{id}/{anything} ← absorbs /{id} on 2.61.0\n            └── news/\n                └── +page.svelte                              # /{id}/news       ← unaffected\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n`/123` matches `src/routes/(series)/[id]/(view)/(meta)/+page.svelte` in all six column configurations above, as on 2.60.1.\n\n## System info\n\n```text\n@sveltejs/kit:                2.61.0 (broken) / 2.60.1 (works)\nsvelte:                       5.55.9\nvite:                         7.3.3\n@sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte: 6.2.4\nnode:                         22+\nOS:                           macOS 25.5 (also reproduces on Linux per production discovery)\n```\n\n## Severity\n\nannoyance — silent 302 on a high-traffic route is a production-visible regression for any app using nested route groups around a `[param]/+page.svelte` leaf. The only safe workaround we found is to flatten one route-group level, which is a non-trivial restructure for established route trees.\n\n## Related\n\n- [#15861](https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/15861) (suspected — routing precedence change for optional rest params)\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15901/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15901/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/issues/2596","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/issues/2596/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/issues/2596/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/issues/2596/events","html_url":"https://github.com/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/issues/2596","id":4425641266,"node_id":"I_kwDOQzKqeM8AAAABB8ntMg","number":2596,"title":"fix(deps): vite 8.0.12 + vite-plugin-svelte + rolldown breaks website build","user":{"login":"williamzujkowski","id":14303249,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzAzMjQ5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/14303249?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski","html_url":"https://github.com/williamzujkowski","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/williamzujkowski/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":9929506774,"node_id":"LA_kwDOQzKqeM8AAAACT9g_1g","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/labels/bug","name":"bug","color":"d73a4a","default":true,"description":"Something isn't working"},{"id":10253917621,"node_id":"LA_kwDOQzKqeM8AAAACYy5dtQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/labels/dependencies","name":"dependencies","color":"0366d6","default":false,"description":"Pull requests that update a dependency file"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-12T02:07:26Z","updated_at":"2026-05-15T11:17:31Z","closed_at":"2026-05-15T11:17:31Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Symptom\n\nDependabot PR #2594 (production-dependencies, 25 updates) regenerated the lockfile and pulled vite from 8.0.10 → 8.0.12. The website build then dies during astro's bundling step:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n[vite-plugin-svelte] !!! Support for vite 8 beta in vite-plugin-svelte is experimental\n  (rolldown: 1.0.0, vite: 8.0.12) !!!\n  See https://github.com/sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte/issues/1143\nNot implemented\n  Location: node_modules/.../vite/dist/node/chunks/node.js:33864:11\n  at PluginContextImpl.generateBundle (.../vite/dist/node/chunks/node.js:33866:37)\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nReproducible locally on the Dependabot branch; doesn't reproduce on main because main's lockfile still has vite 8.0.10.\n\n## Root cause\n\nUpstream regression in vite 8.0.12 (or in the vite/rolldown/vite-plugin-svelte interaction at that version). vite-plugin-svelte explicitly flags itself as experimental on vite 8 beta — \\`generateBundle\\` calls into a getter that throws \\\"Not implemented\\\".\n\nVerified via \\`pnpm why vite\\`:\n\n- **main**: astro 6.1.9 → vite 8.0.10 (works)\n- **#2594 branch**: astro 6.1.9 → vite 8.0.12 (broken)\n\nThe Dependabot bumps on the same branch include vitest 4.1.5 → 4.1.6, which adds vite 8 as a peer dep and likely contributed to pnpm picking the latest 8.x rather than reusing 8.0.10.\n\n## Options\n\n1. **Pin vite to 8.0.10 via pnpm overrides** in root package.json. Quick. Adds a maintenance burden until upstream fixes — we'd need to revisit when vite 8.0.13+ lands.\n2. **Wait for upstream fix.** vite-plugin-svelte#1143 is the tracking issue. Once vite-plugin-svelte ships proper rolldown support, this clears up.\n3. **Roll vite back to 7.x in overrides.** More aggressive — vite 7 is stable but means astro / vitest see a downgrade.\n\n## Status\n\nClosing #2594 with a pointer to this issue. The next weekly Dependabot run will re-propose the 24 non-breaking bumps; whoever picks it up should apply one of the options above first.\n\n## Links\n\n- Dependabot PR (closed): #2594\n- Upstream tracker: https://github.com/sveltejs/vite-plugin-svelte/issues/1143","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/issues/2596/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nexus-substrate/nexus-agents/issues/2596/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dragomano/svelte-russian/issues/50","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dragomano/svelte-russian","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dragomano/svelte-russian/issues/50/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dragomano/svelte-russian/issues/50/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dragomano/svelte-russian/issues/50/events","html_url":"https://github.com/dragomano/svelte-russian/issues/50","id":4362528841,"node_id":"I_kwDONs1hhs8AAAABBAboSQ","number":50,"title":"docs: fix testing docs (#18163)","user":{"login":"github-actions[bot]","id":41898282,"node_id":"MDM6Qm90NDE4OTgyODI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/15368?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D","html_url":"https://github.com/apps/github-actions","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github-actions%5Bbot%5D/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/github