"issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Describe the problem\n\nCurrently, Remote Functions can do Client Side Boundary Streaming with Snippets:\n```svelte\n<script lang=\"ts\">\n  import { browser } from '$app/environment'\n</script>\n\n{#snippet pending()}\n  <p class=\"skeleton\">loading...</p>\n{/snippet}\n\n<svelte:boundary pending={browser ? pending : undefined}>\n  <p>cars today: {await getCarsCount()}</p>\n</svelte:boundary>\n```\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/15719#issuecomment-4360094521\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/discussions/13897#discussioncomment-16775452\n\nAND there is a beta primative `query.live` (https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/15563) which replaced `query.stream` (https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/14292) for Readable Streams and Real Time (Live) Data.\n\nHowever, there needs to be a way to do SSR Streaming (with Promises) just like [Page Loaders](https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/load#Streaming-with-promises) can do.\n\n@Rich-Harris has said this is on the [TODO list](https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/discussions/13897#discussioncomment-16781318), but I didn't see an official Feature Request for it for us to follow.\n\nJ\n\n### Describe the proposed solution\n\nMaybe `query.ssr` or something.\n\n### Alternatives considered\n\nFor now, the only way to do this is to use a [loader function](https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/load#Streaming-with-promises).\n\nOR, you can load from the client (see above).\n\n\n### Importance\n\nnice to have\n\n### Additional Information\n\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/discussions/4831\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/12304\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/14086\n\nThis is also to CLARIFY for people like me that didn't understand the naming difference.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/r